Choices: A : 1 B : 6 C: 4 D : 7 E: none<n>Output: D<n></br><n><n>### Instruction:Answer the question below.<n><n>In order to test if a given binary string (binary array or binary digits) is a binary palindrome you need to find a digit of the given string that should be invered relative to its position or relative to the string. For example, the binary string 1111110 (binary array) can be invered by invering digit 0 with respect to its position in the string 1010011. In this example the value of digit 1010 (in position 2 of given binary string) should be invered with respect to its position to give the correct result. The value of the digit 011 (position 5) invered with respect ot its position is 100. The palindrome with a digit invered with respect of its position is called reverse of the digit. The palindrome can be written as binary string, a string or a number (e.g. -2221, -2212, 102). <n>It is also possible to invert values of the digits from the right side to the left side or vice-versa. <n><n><n>Input: Binary string for which inverse with respect of its position should be performed for getting the correct palindrome. a ) 0001011, b ) 0110100, c ) 0111001, d ) 0112101, e ) any of the above.<n>Output: d<n>

a ) 200, b ) 150, c ) 160, d ) 170, e ) 180<n>Output: a<n><n>Input: a metallic sheet is of rectangular shape with dimensions 48 m x 36 m. from each of its corners, a square is cut off so as to make an open box. if the length of the square is 8 m, the volume of the box ( in m 3 ) is a ) 3220, b ) 4830, c ) 5120, d ) 6420, e ) none<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: amar takes as much time in running 24 meters as a car takes in covering 60 meters. what will be the distance covered by amar during the time the car covers 2.2 km? a ) 700 m, b ) 500 m, c ) 870 m, d ) 880 m, e ) 840 m<n>Output: d<n><n>Input:Where could you find some large pieces of paper that are not for sale? Choices:  A: cabinet B: computer printer C: suitcase D: office supply store E: artist's studio<n>Output:		A. computer printer - most likely not all 35,790 are going to have what you need so you wouldn't find some large pieces  of paper there. B. Artist's studio - they are very likely to have large sheets in  many different size - paper, canvas, etc.    The suitcase would actually be the most expensive option of  all if not in your house.    E. office supply store - they have them in many of the businesses in your  office building, but not a stand-alone office supply store.    The cabinet in your house. This sounds very specific and  probably not very helpful with finding actual office-size pieces   of paper unless they specifically just happen to throw it away  (that you want).

Choices:  A: boot B: the desert C: loaf of bread D: foot E: hock<n>Output:		Option D<n><n>### Instruction : Answer the following question.<n><n>Input : There were 400 people in a hall, every one of them took some sweets. <n>There are 14 children and 96 adults in that room, <n>The number of sweet was 3 times of the number of children.<n> What is the number of adult?<n>Output :<n><n>Ans. 538<n><n>### Instructions:<n>Answer the following question in words:<n>```<n>An equilateral triangle of sides 12 m is placed upside down and on an identical triangle of sides 15 m. If the third vertex of the latter is in the centre of the first triangle, then the length of the other two equal sides is<n>```<n><n>Ans. : 37.5 m<n>\( 37.5 = 22.5^2 = (15/2)^2 \)<n>\(22.5^3 = (15/3)^3 \Rightarrow 22.5 = 5 \Rightarrow 225 = 5^3\)<n>And since the first triangle is equilateral, by Pythagoras theorem \((12)^2 = 15^2 \Rightarrow 12^2 = 192=15^2-1 \Rightarrow 25^3 -21/2 ^2 = 125- 12=113\)<n><n>### Instructiions<n><n>Answer the following questions in words:<n>```A square is cut out of every edge of a cube. All the resulting squares have the same area. What is the area of the square-shaped surface left after all the cuts?"<n>```<n>Ans. 64<n>```<n>We assume the square from (1,1) to (3,3)<n>Then<n>2*4 = 8 sqrd metre<n>```<n>Total area of all the squares = 27(8 sqrd metre) = 216 sqrd metre<n>Total area of the 1/5 area = 216 - 1/5 216 = 124 sqrd metre<n>So, 1/5 area surface area remaining after all the cuts out = 124 metre sqrd.<n>```

Choices: A) 3 B) -3 C) -1 D) 1 E) 0<n>Output:<n><n># import numpy as np<n>import math<n>import timeit<n>import statistics<n><n>def fib(n):<n>    if n == 0:<n>        return 0<n>    else:<n>        a,b,c = 0,1,1<n>        for i in range(1,n):<n>            a,b,c=b,a+b,%a+c<n>        return a<n><n>def cal(n):<n>    # a, b, c, d, e  will be the parameters.<n>    a,b,c,d,e = (n+1)/6, n//6,60,3,90<n>    return ( ( ((a+b)**3))-a-b )/(2**d*e)<n><n>def fib_av(n):<n>    return (0 if n == 0 else fib(n-1)+fib(n-1))<n><n>def average(fib,cal):<n>    total2 = int(fib_av(20))<n>    total = int(fib(20))<n><n>def main():<n>    TIME_AV = 0 <n>    for i in range(20):<n>        time1 = timeit.timeit(lambda: average(fib, cal), number=1000)<n>        TIME_AV += (time1 - TIME_AV)/i<n><n>    print(round(TIME_AV / 1000000, 1).__abs__(), "seconds")<n><n>main()<n># ======================================================================<n># ========================================= PERSONAL PROGRAMMING ==============<n># ============================ Question 1 ===============================<n># =============================================<n># --------------------------------------------------------<n># -------------------------------------------<n><n>def getMean(input):<n>

Choices :  A : fly   B : buzz  C : move  D : honey  E : help flowers pollenate  Output : D<n><n>Input: A number is called a ‘square’, when it is produced by multiplying exactly another number, or another, ‘square’, itself the square of a square number ; and also by multiplying four, the first number of a triangular system ; or five, which is the first number of a pentangular system; and so of all the first number of the other systems, in order. A number of the form 0,2n is an “ even square ”, the term square being here retained as a technical expression, for if it were discarded, as seems at first to be required, since it has a double meaning ; and we should retain the word “ square, the expression 2n instead of 0,2n would involve the same ambiguity.A “ square number “ is that which is the square of another number. All square numbers are divisible by 4, except the square of 3. “ Odd numbers, triangular numbers or Pentagonal numbers,” and all like, are divisible only by two, three, five, ten; and divisible both by 2, and 5 by 3. But there is another property of even numbers more remarkable than any other ; they all have their own reciprocal in themselves. 1; 2; 4; 6; 8, are respectively divisible by 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and each is the sum of 2 and the square of a prime number. What is the sum of the reciprocal of an even number?<n>Output: D<n>Clarification 1: The input is given as a sequence of integers.<n>Clarification 2 : The output should be in words.<n>Clarification for a particular question (SQ57599)<n>During his school holidays in the summer of 1939, John was sent to live with his grandfather in a remote village near a seashore.John got on well with his grandparents and the other villagers.He went on several country walks

This is called Pigeon Hole Principle. There are 20 choices, 17 are pigeon holes (pigeons perching places).<n><n><n>   -<n><n><n><n>    MCQ 26.  The product of two positive integers is 180. If the LCM of the two numbers, x and y to be 40, find the ratio of x + y to y.<n>* The LCM of the two integers is 40, x, y = 40, 20<n>* so the ratio x + y to y = ( x + y ) / y = 40/20  = 2 to 1<n><n>   -<n>MCQ 27. There are two natural numbers a and b such that their ratio to 19 is ( a + b) / ( a - b). Then what is b / a ?<n>* a and b are 2 natural numbers. <n>* We need to find the ratio of a and b to 19.<n>* Then if it is expressed as the ratio of 19, it is expressed as the difference

Find the circumference of the court to 3 decimal places.<n>Output:26.477<n><n>**Input:**<n><n>**Output:**<n><n>### Solution<n><n>#### Bubble Sort<n><n>```python<n>def bubble_sort(A):<n>  n = len(A)<n>  for i in range(n):<n>    for j in range(i+1, n):<n>      if A[j] < A[j - 1]:<n>        tmp = A[j - 0]<n>        A[j-0] = A[j]<n>        A[n] = tmp<n>```<n>```<n>n = len(A)  #Number of Nodes<n>for i in range(n)<n>    for j in raange(i+1,n)<n>        if A[j] > A[j-1]:  #if the element in index=j(i>=1) > than the element in index = j-1<n>            print(A)<n>            tmp = A[j-1]<n>            A[j-1]= A[j]<n>            A[i]= tmp<n>```<n>Input:<n><n>10,34<n>34,2<n>56,70<n>1,0<n>101,3<n><n>Output:<n><n>34,234,1,34,2,1,3,101,0<n><n>#### Selection Sort<n><n>```python <n>def selection_sort(A):  <n>  for i in A:  #Traversing the array from left to right<n>      min = i #Index of smallest<n>      for j in range(1, i.size):<n>        if A[min] > A[j]:<n>          min = j<n>      exchange(min, i) <n>        <n>def exchange(i, j):<n>        tem=A[i]<n>

A. integers and numbers B. even numbers and fractional numbers C. irrational numbers and natural numbers D. prime numbers and composite numbers E. prime and even numbers<n>Output: A<n>				<n>Input: When a group of numbers is written with a plus sign (+), it's called a set. It contains numbers with and numbers (with or without decimals or fractions) as well as symbols. A plus sign (+) tells us that these numbers can add to make a total. For example: (0)0 + 2 + 4 + (5 - 4 -1) + 6 = 22. The 0 in this is a placeholder number. The plus (+) signs show that all these numbers can add to get 22. A plus sign (+)+ is sometimes used instead of + to show two or more numbers. A plus sign (+). sign shows that all the set of numbers can be added to get a total. A plus sign (+).. sign shows that all the numbers in the set can be added to make the total that comes after it. Numbers that don't have a plus sign (+.) aren't added together. What are number sets? A. Natural numbers B. Composite numbers C. Placeholder numbers

Then they will line up, 1st group: 4th and 5th person, 2nd group: 3rd and 4th person, 3rd group: 2nd and 3rd person. What will the order of the people in the line line up in, assuming the coins tossed were 99, 85, 40, 8, and 60, 20, 59, 2

She might not need the additional protection that the first pair offers, but on the other hand, we don’t need to risk one of her family member getting an ankle injury. Choices:  A: relaxation B: exhaustion C: energetic D: become stronger E: use energy<n>Output:		A<n><n># Code for Solution:<n> <n># 1 -> 140<n> <n>def main():<n>	n = int(input())<n>	if n == 140:<n>		return 151<n>	else:<n>		return False<n>		<n>	return False<n>	<n># 2 -> 2302<n>	 <n>def main(): <n>	n = int ( input () )<n><n>	if (n * n-2 * n + 3 - ( (n-1) ) ** 2 ) < 1: <n>		return 2302 <n><n>	else: <n>		<n>		return False <n>		<n>return False <n><n># 3 -> 2304<n> <n>def main (): <n><n>	n = int()<n>	<n>	if ( ( ( n * n - 2 * n +1- ((n-1) )**2) > 0.000001 and n not in [1,2,4] ] ): <n><n>		# n = 4; n^4 = 200, n^3-((n-1)**2) = 22<n><n>		n = int(4) <n><n>		d = n ** 2- 4 * n + 2 <n><n>		if d < 0 and d > 0.01: <n><n>			return 2 ** ( int(math.sqrt(d) ) )  <n><n>		return False  <n><n>	return False <n><n><n># 4 -> 8640<n><n><n>def main () : <n>	v = int (input ())<n><n>	# v: the volume to be inscribed<n><n>	v = int (+v)<n><n>	print (v)<n><n>	z = 1  <n><n>	l = v * z<n><n>	if v > 50: <n><n>	if v >= 19: <n><n>	z = l / 500 <n><n>	else : <n><n>	return False<n><n>return z<n><n># 5 -> 9640<n><n> <n>def main () :  <n>	n = int ()<n><n>	print(n)
